		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>This byeshk spike can change size and shape into several bladed forms. It is deadly against aberrant creatures.</i></p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Weapon</b><b>:</b> Broadsword, dagger, longsword, shuriken or short sword</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Enhancement Bonus:</b> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Critical:</b> +2d6 critical damage, +2d10 critical damage against aberrant creatures</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Property:</b></p> <p>You gain a +1 item bonus to all defenses against the attacks of aberrant creatures.</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power (Minor Action)</b></p><p><i>Effect:</i> Ashurta's blade takes the shape of a broadsword (Adventurer's Vault, page 9), dagger, longsword, shuriken, or short sword. It takes on the statistics normal for that weapon until it changes shape into another weapon.</p><p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power âœ¦ Daily (Free Action)</b></p><p><i>Trigger:</i> You hit with an attack using the weapon.</p><p><i>Effect:</i> A target of the attack is dazed until the end of your next turn. An aberrant creature is also restrained and cannot teleport until the end of your next turn.</p>",
